A Race Against the Clock

Is what it feels like. Have you ever seen House or Smile?

- emotional suppression as survival mechanisms

I'm so hell-bent on _not_ being terrible (because of all of the intrusive thoughts), that when I attempted to prove myself not terrible, I end up making it worse. 

What I need is to feel. So it's a race between suicide and being able to feel which will allow me to take control of my life. I don't exactly feel suicidal, but I know it'll happen, I know I keep running from how terrible my life is, so it goes on.

That's exactly how it goes: I keep trying to escape this terrible premonition (you can't even know the future!), that I run into proving it true. Have you ever read Kafka on the shore?

Well, certainly I'm not in control of my actions, so it's a race now. Whether these increasingly sparse and increasingly (but not depicted to those I reach out to) cries for help, will allow me to take control to a certain extent that will allow me to live. I fear that they won't.

What I wish for is tough love, I wish for someone to tell me: "You've just got to fucking do it. Without a reason. Despite all the voices in your head telling you the wrong shit. Because it's fucking possible, all there is is action depsite."

